  <body>
    <%- include("partials/header-musa") %>

    <main>
      <section class="py-3">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="mb-5">
            <a href="/" class="back-to-home" aria-label="Back to home page">
              <i class="bi bi-arrow-90deg-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </a>
            <h2 class="d-inline">Info & Support</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-5">
            <h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
            <p>
              At MUSA, we respect your privacy. 
              <br>We do not collect any personally identifiable data. Information provided through our contact form is used only to respond to your inquiries and is not stored, shared, or reused for any other purpose.
              <br>We do not record or store any audio input from features like speech-to-text. Any data collected automatically (such as usage analytics) is used solely to improve accessibility, functionality, and the overall user experience.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-5">
            <h3>Terms of Use</h3>
            <p>
              By using the MUSA web app, you agree to use its content for personal, non-commercial purposes only. We are not responsible for the content of external websites or third-party services accessed through our platform.
              <br><br>Our speech-to-text feature is designed as an assistive tool to enhance communication accessibility. 
              Due to platform limitations, it functions best on Google Chrome, Edge and Opera. On iOS devices, the Speech Recognition API is not fully supported in browsers. As a result, we guide users to use the built-in microphone feature within the iOS keyboard instead.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-5 access-stm">
            <h3>Accessibility Statement</h3>
            <p>
              MUSA is committed to digital accessibility for all users, especially Deaf individuals who communicate using Irish Sign Language (ISL).
              We provide interpretive ISL videos, support screen readers, and prioritize mobile-first, inclusive design practices.
              If you encounter any barriers while using the platform, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>. We will do our best to address your concerns promptly.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
